little panda a young child's english chinese bilingual friend learning design and technology skip to main content skip to main navigation stanford university school of education learning design and technology home ma programs suse stanford search this site about ldt academics admissions our students faculty & research ldt home home our students master's projects little panda a young child's english chinese bilingual friend little panda a young child's english chinese bilingual friend project by minette chan josie shui hui chou project year 2002 little panda is a portable learning device for children ages 4 to 6 growing up in a predominantly english speaking environment young children of asian immigrants in the united states are usually exposed to their parents native language during their early years but frequently lose interest in acquiring their heritage language when they reach school age often because of its perceived lack of usefulness and coolness little panda helps these children acquire chinese language proficiency and appreciate chinese culture it is pedagogically designed to maximize learnability and motivation by adding attractive elements of songs games story telling and interactive lessons to scaffold the child's learning process our students student portfolios master's projects life after ldt gallery of master's projects 2011 2010 2009 2008 2007 2006 2005 2004 2003 2002 2001 2000 1999 stanford university school of education 485 lasuen mall stanford ca 94305 3096 tel 650 723 2109 copyright 2012 stanford university all rights reserved site map contact suse admissions helpsu maps & directions suse it axess academic calendar stanford bulletin office of the registrar edmail stanfordwho stanfordyou login connect with us connect with us on facebook connect with us on twitter connect with us on youtube connect with us on flickr website by lyudmila christie suse it
